<br>
Training however is WRONG.  Deathly wrong.  While any OOC insults from either side are wrong, the raid essentially did nothing that was out of the ordinary.  They came in, killed a few non critical background NPCs, and did about the same that any other city raid would do.  Yelled a few shouted insults etc etc etc.  Sure, challenge it if you will, duel them.<br>
<br>
However, making excuses for training, and the act of training itself are indeed wrong.  Entirely.  Regardless of which party started it, the anvil is over the head of the Sisters of Myth here and rightly so.<br>
<br>
Absolutely nothing against Vivienne OOC.  She's a great roleplayer and a real joy to roleplay with and talk to.  However, I get the feeling she was being fed false information here and really didn't have a clue what in the name of blue bloody hell was going on. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uaailin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aailin </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/4/02 9:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sister of Myth...dishonored and griefers</span><hr size=1> The tell I sent didn't say they were bad roleplayers...It said we were trained which is not a Roleplaying thing to do.  After I saw I was getting nowher I expressed my shock that a supposed RP guild would do that.  We never claimed to be strict roleplayers far from it.  Our chat in guild and group is alwayss ooc right or wrong thats the way we handle it.<br>
