<br>
There are at least two sides to every story. This forum is at best a very rudimentary judicial process... People are entitled to their opinions, obviously, but everyone should bear in mind that what you read isnt necessarily what happened. There has already been someone who vouched that things went on around the section of the log that was presented, and one of the two main players has yet to speak up. <br>
<br>
Bear in mind as well that opinions expressed in The Soapbox do not necessarily reflect those of the characters, or of any guild. Officers are allowed to have IRL opinions. That doesnt necessarily mean their characters will act on them, nor does it mean they are an evil person if they disagree with you. <br>
<br>
Most of what people are arguing about seems to boil down to a few issues:<br>
<br>
#1] Training: There is no debate as to whether it is against the rules. Ive seen this happen in city zones so many times I would expect it as well, but that doesnt make it right. Still, lets keep perspective on this. Someone had to zone because of a train. I can understand people objecting to it, but yeesh. <br>
<br>
#2] People should reread the most recent guild string involving AS, where a number of people spoke out in support of AS, saying that the whole guild shouldnt be held responsible for the actions of a few bad apples. Are some guilds allowed to have a few bad apples and others not? Just making a point here. We dont even know that a &quot;bad apple&quot; exists yet in Sisters, or what measures will be taken if one does, but we should apply consistent standards to all guilds.<br>
<br>
3] People should cut Vivienne some slack. Give her a chance to think and respond. It was what... 2 AM? Maybe she said some things she didnt mean, maybe some of what she said didnt come out the way she wanted. We all know how late nights complicate things.<br>
<br>
My advice? Take two aspirin and call me in the morning. Give the Sisters a chance to respond... and consider what happened in the overall scheme of things.<br>
